# 📈 MarketWatch — Equity Risk Analytics

> An end-to-end Python pipeline that ingests market data, persists it to SQL, computes 
> portfolio risk metrics (Value-at-Risk & volatility), and serves it through an 
> interactive dashboard.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10+-blue)
![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Streamlit-dashboard-red)
![SQLite](https://img.shields.io/badge/SQLite-database-green)
![Tests](https://img.shields.io/badge/tests-pytest-orange)




---

## 🎯 Overview

MarketWatch demonstrates a complete data analytics workflow that mirrors how risk and 
analytics teams operate in practice: **fetch → clean → store in SQL → query → analyze → visualize.**

It computes the core risk metrics used on banking and trading floors:
- **Historical Value-at-Risk (VaR)** — the loss threshold on the worst *X%* of trading days
- **Conditional VaR (CVaR / Expected Shortfall)** — the *average* loss in that tail
- **Annualized rolling volatility** — risk measured over a configurable window

---

## ✨ Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| 📥 **Data Ingestion** | Pulls live historical price data from Yahoo Finance for any set of tickers |
| 🗄️ **SQL Persistence** | Stores tidy data in SQLite with an indexed `prices` table for fast lookups |
| 📊 **Risk Modeling** | Historical VaR & CVaR, configurable confidence levels (90/95/99%) |
| 📈 **Volatility Analysis** | Rolling annualized volatility using log returns × √252 |
| 🖥️ **Interactive Dashboard** | Streamlit app with adjustable tickers, periods, and position sizing |
| ✅ **Tested** | Unit tests covering the financial math (pytest) |

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Language:** Python 3.10+
**Data:** pandas, NumPy, yfinance
**Database:** SQLite (via `sqlite3`)
**Visualization:** Streamlit, Matplotlib
**Testing:** pytest

